import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['home_score'] = pd.to_numeric(data['home_score'], errors='coerce')
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='home_score', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['home_score'].mean(), color='red', label='Mean: {:.2f}'.format(data['home_score'].mean()))
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of home scores?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['score_diff'] = data['home_score'] - data['away_score']
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='score_diff', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['score_diff'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Mean Score Difference: {:.2f}'.format(data['score_diff'].mean()))
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of score difference?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['team'] = data['home_team'].fillna(data['away_team'])
    data['score'] = data['home_score'].fillna(0) + data['away_score'].fillna(0)
    data = data.groupby('team')['score'].mean().reset_index()
    data = data.sort_values(by='score', ascending=False)
    chart = sns.barplot(x='team', y='score', data=data, palette='Blues_d')
    chart.set_xticklabels(chart.get_xticklabels(), rotation=90)
    plt.title('Which teams have the highest average score?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data.sort_values(by='date')
    sns.lineplot(x='date', y='home_score', data=data, label='Home Score')
    sns.lineplot(x='date', y='away_score', data=data, label='Away Score')
    plt.title('What is the trend of scores over time?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
